<DocsLayout title="Revenue Tracking - Infinity Metrics">
  <h1>Revenue Tracking</h1>
  <p>
    Track e-commerce transactions and revenue attribution to understand the
    impact of your marketing efforts.
  </p>

  <h2>Basic Revenue Tracking</h2>
  <p>Track a purchase event:</p>
  <pre><code>Infinity.track('purchase', &#123;
  value: 99.99,
  currency: 'USD',
  transaction_id: 'txn_123456'
&#125;);</code></pre>

  <h2>E-commerce Events</h2>
  <p>Track the complete purchase funnel:</p>
  <pre><code>// Add to cart
Infinity.track('add_to_cart', &#123;
  product_id: 'prod_123',
  price: 29.99,
  quantity: 1
&#125;);

// Begin checkout
Infinity.track('begin_checkout', &#123;
  cart_value: 89.97,
  items: 3
&#125;);

// Purchase complete
Infinity.track('purchase', &#123;
  value: 89.97,
  currency: 'USD',
  transaction_id: 'txn_123456'
&#125;);</code></pre>

  <h2>Revenue Attribution</h2>
  <p>
    Understand which marketing channels drive the most revenue by tracking the
    complete customer journey from first visit to purchase.
  </p>

  <h2>Common Properties</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>value</strong> - Transaction amount</li>
    <li><strong>currency</strong> - Currency code (USD, EUR, etc.)</li>
    <li><strong>transaction_id</strong> - Unique transaction identifier</li>
    <li><strong>product_id</strong> - Product identifier</li>
    <li><strong>quantity</strong> - Number of items</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Next: <a href="/docs/subdomain-tracking">Subdomain Tracking</a></p>
</DocsLayout>
